-- Shareholders Call for Omega Insurance Overhaul, Telegraph Says
-- B y   B e n   M o s h i n s k y
-- 2012-04-22T08:46:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/shareholders-call-for-omega-insurance-overhaul-telegraph-says.html
Shareholders in Omega Insurance
Holdings Ltd. called for an emergency general meeting to
overhaul the company’s board, the Sunday Telegraph reported,
citing activist investment fund Crystal Amber Fund Ltd.  Some shareholders, including Artemis Asset Management and
Toscafund Asset Management, are dissatisfied with the
performance of Omega’s senior executives, according to the
report. Omega declined to comment, the Telegraph said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Moshinsky in London at 
 bmoshinsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
